# Audit opencode/codex/crush MCP tool interfaces from ref-projects/

Read the source code in `ref-projects/` for opencode, codex, crush, and any other
relevant coding CLIs. For each project, extract the MCP tool definitions for tools
such as: `bash`/`execute_shell`, `edit`/`str_replace`, `glob`/`find`, `read`/`cat`,
`write`, `list`/`ls`, and agent spawning / subagent tools.

## Requirements

- Read ref-projects/ for: opencode, codex, crush, and any others present
- For each tool type in each project, record:
  - Tool name
  - Input parameter names and types
  - Parameter descriptions (verbatim if possible)
  - Return value structure
  - Any notable UX affordances (e.g. line-range reading, dry-run mode, etc.)
- Focus on: bash/exec, file read, file write, file edit, glob/find, list dir, spawn subagent

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] All relevant ref-projects/ CLIs audited for MCP tool definitions
- [ ] Each tool type catalogued with parameter names, types, and descriptions
- [ ] Notable UX patterns and affordances documented per tool per CLI
- [ ] Output stored as a markdown document in docs/ or as a finding in T002
- [ ] Covers at minimum: bash/exec, read, write, edit, glob, list, spawn-agent tools
